         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Botanic Road Adelaide ¶ May 9th 1876 ¶ My dear Baron ¶  ¶ I send herewith a complete plant It is a tolerably typical specimen. Luxurious plants are sometimes 3 or 4 times wider and a foot taller but t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">76.05.09a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Alexander Paterson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Library, Royal Botanic Gardens<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Dittrichia graveolens</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(MEL 2073205).</p>
               </note>Botanic Road Adelaide</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">May 9th 1876</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I send herewith a complete plant It is a tolerably typical specimen. Luxurious plants are sometimes 3 or 4 times wider and a foot taller but this shows the habit pretty well. It is called stink weed<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also A. Paterson to M, 24 April 1876.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>here why I dont know as the smell is strong but not disagreeable I cant say where it came from, but it is spreading all over the cultivated lands, and imparts its own odour to the atmosphere in places where it is abundant. Till lately my own impression has been that it is indigenous. The florets of the ray and disk are distinctly and pronouncedly<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">yellow</hi>
               </seg>. The anthers have tails, which I observed under the microscope after carefully dissecting a tubular floret. I have remarked it in the vicinity of Adelaide for at least the last 4 years.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Very truly Yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Alex S Paterson</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Many thanks for your enclosures.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's letter and enclosures not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Before sending the list of plants to the Surveyor General I took the liberty of copying it which I trust you will not disapprove. I may say that Mr Goyder is away in Tasmania at present I know Dr Davies and will take an early opportunity of urging him to fulfil his promise to obtain for you one of the 16 sets of Schultz's Port Darwin plants so far as the 3d sending is concerned.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e., F. Schultze. He sent a five consignments of plant ansd animal specimens to Adelaide during his 1869-70 stay in the Northern Territory. The third consignment was despatched on 28 September 1869<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Wallis (2020). M requested a set in M to R. Schomburk, 15 November 1869 and M to G. Goyder, 15 November 1869 (in this edition as 69-11-15a).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M did not receive a full set:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">b</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ecause of M's 'excentrick behaviour towards me' Schomburgk deliberately kept from M</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">any unique specimens, which instead he sent to Kew</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">in</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">their</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">set</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">(R. Schomburgk to G. Bentham, 19 August 1869, in this edition as M69-08-16).</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">A. Paterson to M, 24 April 1876 M<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>had evidently asked for Paterson's help in obtaining a complete set.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I am truly sorry to learn that no improvement has as yet taken place in your position</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">ASP</p>
         </div>
